{
  "stem": "7506.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were no telephone conversations, as we didn't have a telephone.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That wouldn't have been allowed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But we did-- my mother did write to my grandmother through the Red Cross.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The reason I know that is because of the two letters that were given to Jopi's father, which we got back after the war.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Those two letters are in the Washington Museum.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I donated them.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They were special form letter both in German and Dutch.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "One side was written by the sender.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The other side was written by the return addressee.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So the letter has both-- it's one piece of paper, both sides.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I have photocopies, but the originals are in Washington.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Where my mother wrote to her mother.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] [SOBBING] And my-- my grandmother wrote back to my mother in Dutch.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Because that was my grandmother's language, really.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Because she had come from Holland, of course, many years before the war.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "That was the only correspondence.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And the correspondence consists of about, you know, three very short-- four short sentences. 'We are well.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Kisses from the children.' That's all.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "That's all.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Because all that mail must have been censored, I'm sure.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] That's the only-- that's the only contact my parents and my mother, in this instance, had with her family in-- in England.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] The other thing my mother started to do when we were living in the Jewish quarter-- [SIGHS] my friend's father had gotten for my parents [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] cloth of a khaki color.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And from that, my mother made a rucksack for each of us-- for my sister, and my father, and my mother, myself.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And also a shoulder bag of the same material.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "My mother had made that.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
